text: Locke is an unincorporated community in Pend Oreille County, in the U.S. state of Washington. ==History== A post office called Locke was established in 1900, and remained in operation until it was discontinued in 1954. The community was named for John Locke. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Pend Oreille County, Washington Category:Unincorporated communities in Washington (state)
title: Locke, Washington
